# Institute of Digital Risk (IDR) – Brand & Homepage

A high-fidelity brand identity and responsive homepage built for the **Institute of Digital Risk (IDR)**. This project demonstrates fundamental web development skills using semantic HTML5, modern CSS (Grid/Flexbox), and vanilla JavaScript, following a strict "no-frameworks" requirement.


## Desktop View

![Desktop View](assets/image.png)

## Mobile View

![Mobile View](assets/image-1.png)


## Features

**Custom Brand Identity**: A minimalist logo designed to symbolize structure, risk, and resilience using a geometric cube.


**Semantic HTML5**: Utilizes structural tags like `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, and `<footer>` for accessibility and SEO.


**Responsive Design**: A mobile-first layout that adapts seamlessly to desktop and mobile screens using CSS Grid and Flexbox.
+1

**Modern Interactivity**:

* Sticky navigation bar with glassmorphism effects.
* Smooth scrolling to internal sections.
* Interactive hover states for buttons and navigation links.


## Design Philosophy

* **Typography**: Clean sans-serif (Inter) to provide a modern, academic feel.
* **Color Palette**: A bold combination of **Vibrant Orange**, **Stark White**, and **Deep Black**.
* **Symbolism**: The isometric cube represents the multi-dimensional nature of digital risk and the stability provided by IDR’s training.

## Tech Stack

* **HTML5** (Semantic structure) 
* **CSS3** (Custom Properties, Grid, Flexbox) 
* **Vanilla JavaScript** (Navigation logic and form handling)

## Project Structure
```paintext
/IDR-Project
├── index.html       # Homepage structure
├── style.css        # Responsive layouts and branding
├── script.js        # UI interactions
└── /assets          # Logo variants and imagery
```
## Design Note

### Logo
![Logo](assets/image-3.png)

### Logo with Text
![Logo with Text](assets/image-2.png)

The logo utilizes an isometric cube to symbolize the structured approach to managing complex digital risks and the resilience of protected infrastructure. The vibrant orange was selected to represent the proactive nature of the institute, contrasted with a minimalist black-and-white palette to ensure an academic and professional aesthetic. The clean typography ensures high legibility across all digital platforms.